            <div class="faq-a">Mixed-use residential mortgages are possible but with restrictions. If the property is primarily residential with a portion used for practice space (typical home-office acupuncture studio), standard conventional residential mortgages apply. If the property is primarily commercial with residential component, commercial financing is required. The dividing line is usually 50%+ residential use. We assess the use case and identify the right financing structure.</div>
